.TH "sock_recvmsg" 9 "sock_recvmsg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sock_recvmsg \- receive a message from @sock
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sock_recvmsg
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *msg "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket
.IP "msg" 12
message to receive
.IP "flags" 12
message flags

Receives \fImsg\fP from \fIsock\fP, passing through LSM. Returns the total number
of bytes received, or an error.
